# Trivy CVE suppressions with rationale.
#
# Each entry must include a justification comment so any future scan
# triage can audit why the CVE is suppressed and re-evaluate when the
# rationale no longer holds. Format: a comment block, then one CVE id
# per line.

# ─── libarchive13t64: not reached by Mangarr's import pipeline ───────
# Mangarr handles RAR archives (manga CBR files) via the Python
# `rarfile` library. `rarfile` shells out to the `unrar` binary
# (provided by the Debian `unrar-free` package) — a separate codebase
# from libarchive. The vulnerable RAR5 / ISO9660 decompression code in
# libarchive is not on Mangarr's call path.
#
# libarchive is still installed because `unrar-free` declares it as a
# transitive dependency, but no Mangarr code (or the unrar binary
# itself) invokes it. Re-evaluate if the import pipeline ever switches
# to a Python binding that links libarchive directly (e.g.
# python-libarchive-c).
#
# Re-check: each Mangarr release; remove a line if Debian ships a fix.
CVE-2026-4111
CVE-2026-4424
CVE-2026-5121
